00:12:58.500 --> 00:13:00.300
Or when you're looking
at speaker details,

00:13:00.300 --> 00:13:03.380
the speaker avatars, the
photos of the speakers,

00:13:03.380 --> 00:13:04.900
are in those margins.

00:13:04.900 --> 00:13:07.030
So I kind of look
at it that way.

00:13:07.030 --> 00:13:10.390
And it does, again,
help for scanning.

00:13:10.390 --> 00:13:12.990
It's very easy to, once you
lay that one piece of text

00:13:12.990 --> 00:13:17.900
on the screen, just look all
the way down and very quickly

00:13:17.900 --> 00:13:19.805
scan the rest of
the text related

00:13:19.805 --> 00:13:21.030
to that first piece of text.

00:13:21.030 --> 00:13:24.392
In this case, the title,
description, and so on,

00:13:24.392 --> 00:13:26.864
and the metadata as
well for the session.

00:13:26.864 --> 00:13:28.530
NICK BUTCHER: And
another thing I really

00:13:28.530 --> 00:13:30.920
liked about using the key
lines in our design process,

00:13:30.920 --> 00:13:33.840
it was a very easy way to
bake in some responsive design

00:13:33.840 --> 00:13:35.749
principles into layouts.

00:13:35.749 --> 00:13:38.040
So in these screenshots here,
you can see, for example,

00:13:38.040 --> 00:13:39.789
we've called out what
the key lines should

00:13:39.789 --> 00:13:41.144
be on a smaller device.

00:13:41.144 --> 00:13:42.560
But then, you can
very easily just

00:13:42.560 --> 00:13:44.830
increase these key
lines on larger devices

00:13:44.830 --> 00:13:47.940
and build in this
kind of responsiveness

00:13:47.940 --> 00:13:49.680
from upfront
thinking about where

00:13:49.680 --> 00:13:51.200
the different
blocks of text are.

00:13:51.200 --> 00:13:53.120
You're designing
the use of content

00:13:53.120 --> 00:13:55.581
and the use of white
space deliberately.

00:13:55.581 --> 00:13:57.330
And then, you can then
vary those amounts,

00:13:57.330 --> 00:14:00.630
the way they scale up as you
have more space on a device.

00:14:00.630 --> 00:14:02.880
ROMAN NURIK: The other thing
I wanted to mention here,

00:14:02.880 --> 00:14:04.296
and yeah, that
totally makes sense

00:14:04.296 --> 00:14:07.220
to me, the responsive nature,
