00:14:17.260 --> 00:14:20.600
And this has been around
on Android for a while

00:14:20.600 --> 00:14:24.040
using a 4 DIP or an 8 DIP grid.

00:14:24.040 --> 00:14:27.820
In this case, everything
in material design,

00:14:27.820 --> 00:14:32.410
all the suggested values,
they fall on that grid.

00:14:32.410 --> 00:14:36.360
It makes it really
easy to I guess

00:14:36.360 --> 00:14:38.970
diverge from the guidelines
when you feel it's necessary,

00:14:38.970 --> 00:14:40.050
when you need to.

00:14:40.050 --> 00:14:42.330
So these 16 DIPs,
the 72 DIPs, these

00:14:42.330 --> 00:14:43.840
are just suggested guidelines.

00:14:43.840 --> 00:14:46.560
But if you need a bit more
space in that left margin,

00:14:46.560 --> 00:14:49.430
it's really easy to say,
let me try to add 8 DIPs.

00:14:49.430 --> 00:14:51.260
Let me try to add 16
DIPs to that key line

00:14:51.260 --> 00:14:54.490
and see if that kind of
better communicates my content

00:14:54.490 --> 00:14:58.650
or gives my content more space
to breathe or whatever it is.

00:14:58.650 --> 00:15:00.580
And so I kind of look
at material design

00:15:00.580 --> 00:15:04.650
and these key lines specifically
