00:35:54.580 --> 00:35:56.860
In addition to that,
the typographic scale

00:35:56.860 --> 00:35:59.220
that Nick was just
talking about,

00:35:59.220 --> 00:36:01.360
if you don't use
the material spec

00:36:01.360 --> 00:36:05.950
recommended typographic
scale, create your own.

00:36:05.950 --> 00:36:08.870
Don't have a million
different font

00:36:08.870 --> 00:36:13.100
sizes and weights
and attributes.

00:36:13.100 --> 00:36:16.270
Be consistent and be
purposeful in your deviations

00:36:16.270 --> 00:36:18.159
from the spec.

00:36:18.159 --> 00:36:19.700
ROMAN NURIK: I guess
one thing to add

00:36:19.700 --> 00:36:22.720
there is while we're on
the topic of typography,

00:36:22.720 --> 00:36:25.470
a big part of your
brand is typography.

00:36:25.470 --> 00:36:28.815
And so in material design,
we talk a lot about Roboto

00:36:28.815 --> 00:36:33.755
and we have very specific styles
for headline text and body

00:36:33.755 --> 00:36:35.769
text, and they're all
basically using Roboto.

00:36:35.769 --> 00:36:37.560
It doesn't mean that
Roboto is the only way

00:36:37.560 --> 00:36:39.140
to design an Android app.

00:36:39.140 --> 00:36:43.320
A lot of great, really well
designed Android apps today

00:36:43.320 --> 00:36:45.640
use different typefaces.

00:36:45.640 --> 00:36:47.280
And material design is the same.

00:36:47.280 --> 00:36:49.820
You don't necessarily
have to use Roboto.

00:36:49.820 --> 00:36:53.920
You should probably
use pretty good

00:36:53.920 --> 00:36:57.540
looking sans serif typefaces.

00:36:57.540 --> 00:37:03.170
You probably should avoid using
too many serifs in your apps.

00:37:03.170 --> 00:37:05.060
But it's definitely
something where

00:37:05.060 --> 00:37:09.320
that is an area where you
should be true to your brand.

00:37:09.320 --> 00:37:12.920
You shouldn't try to force your
brand into Roboto unless you

00:37:12.920 --> 00:37:16.730
feel like it is harmonious
with your brand.

00:37:16.730 --> 00:37:19.172
So yeah, that's just another
thing that we thought about.

00:37:19.172 --> 00:37:21.630
Obviously, Roboto makes a lot
of sense for Google products.

00:37:21.630 --> 00:37:23.530
But a lot of other
apps, it's not

00:37:23.530 --> 00:37:25.060
a necessity you have to use it.

00:37:25.060 --> 00:37:26.710
We think it looks great, though.

00:37:26.710 --> 00:37:28.767
One other thing I guess
on the concept of type,

00:37:28.767 --> 00:37:31.350
and I guess we may have talked
about some previous [INAUDIBLE]

00:37:31.350 --> 00:37:34.990
or maybe not, but when
you do choose a typeface,

00:37:34.990 --> 00:37:38.170
it's important to test
